         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Royal Herbarium ¶ Kew London ¶ June 12 /72 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ I have to acknowledge yours of the 18th March — the case you mention has not yet come to hand but I presume will make its appearance ere l...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.06.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne. </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Royal Herbarium</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Kew London</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">June 12 /72</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to acknowledge yours of the 18th March — the case you mention has not yet come to hand but I presume will make its appearance ere long</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have finished the <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name> and a box with your specimens is just packed and will I believe be dispatched in a day or two</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With regard to supplementary matter for the previous volumes I must not think of that — It will be as much as I can do to get through the Monocotyledons if even I am spared long enough to finish them — besides supplements to portions of a work before the whole is finished are always exceedingly inconvenient for those who have to work with the book — The <name key="Thymeleae">Thymeleae</name>
               <name key="Santalaceae">Santalaceae</name> and <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name> for the present volume make up about 320 species the remaining Dicotyledons may yield some 300 more which will leave room for about 600 Monocotyledons and I hope enable us to get the remaining Monocotyledons all into the 7th volume.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Of Bentham (1863-78).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There have been several impediments to getting out any more of Hooker's Icones — great trouble with getting the artists to work etc — but the series is now going on the first part of the 12th vol will be out in a few days. It contains chiefly <name key="Compositae">Compositae</name> and <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name> — amongst others I have had your <name key="Coleocoma">Coleocoma</name> and <name key="Thespidium">Thespidium</name> figured (in the 2d part of the volume now also far advanced) — also an interesting new genus of <name key="Bombaceae">Bombaceae</name> from Schultz's Port Darwin plants which Dr Masters has published as <name key="Camptostemon%20Schultzii">Camptostemon Schultzii</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1867-89), vol. 12, pp. 33 and pl. 1136, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>39 and pl. 1143, 18 and pl. 1119 respectively.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am also having figured Schultz's no. 639 a Leguminous plant allied to <name key="Crotalaria">Crotalaria</name> but with a very different carina and pod I had it from Cunningham but not in a state to characterise satisfactorily so I passed it over — we have now flowers and fruit — and I think I must make a new genus of it.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Plagiocarpus axillaris</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in J. Hooker (1867-89), vol. 12, p. 56, pl. 1162. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We have no controul<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">sic</seg>.</p>
               </note> over the publishers as to the advertisements they stick on to the books. I presume they find it pay which to them is more important than the convenience of the purchasers.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are now sending genera<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 2, part 1.</p>
               </note> to press so that I shall do but little more to Flora Australiensis the next three months</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron F. v. Mueller</p>
